The Minister of State for Health, Olorunmimbe Mamora, on Friday, congratulated the standard flag bearer of the All Progressives Congress for the 2023 presidential election, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu. Mamora, in a statement he personally signed, attributed Tinubu’s victory to “courage, vision and strategy.” The minister stated, “This is to congratulate you on your well deserved emergence as the presidential flag bearer of the All Progressives Congress for the 2023 presidential election. “You have come a long way in your political career, demonstrating courage, vision and strategy, the three attributes that I have always believed stand you out among your peers. Your resilience even in the face of seemingly daunting odds has been legendary. “You have led from the front as a leader and have come this far to the glory of God. The real battle still lies ahead in 2023. As you march on with confidence, may your troops be willing on your day of battle and may God’s purpose for your life be fulfilled.” At the APC presidential primary on Tuesday and Wednesday, Tinubu garnered 1,271 votes to clinch the party’s presidential ticket, while the immediate past Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, got 316 votes; Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo, 235 votes; a former Minister of State for Education,  Chukwuemeka Nwajiuba, one vote; Senator Rochas Okorocha and Pastor Tunde Bakare got zero vote each.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com